XD Bar
-------
A minialistic statusbar for X11 Desktops, compatible with EWMH standards.
Inspired by 'X'mobar and 'D'wm statusbar, written in 'C'.

Why C? performance.
If so, why not Rust? No official X11 lib, writing FFI for X11 was delightfully
painful.
Future Goals: Rewrite in Rust. :pepehands:

Build and install:
------------------
  make && sudo make install

Build Requirements:
-------------------
  - GNU Make
  - libx11
  - libxft
  - fontconfig

How it renders:
---------------

  ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
  |stdin                                                                WM_NAME|
  ------------------------------------------------------------------------------

  'stdin' text is typically provided by the window manager
  'WM_NAME' (of the root window) can be set using the 'xsetroot' command.

Setting 'WM_NAME':
------------------
  - slstatus <https://tools.suckless.org/slstatus>
  - xdstatus (better than slstatus) <https://github.com/lycuid/xdstatus>

  - Custom script example (using bash):

    #!/bin/bash
    while true; do
      xsetroot -name "$(whoami)@$(hostname) on $(uname -o) | $(date)"
      sleep(1)
    done

Styling text:
-------------
  Template for styling text:
    <Tag:Extension=Val> Text </Tag>

  Valid Tags:
    Fn, Fg, Bg, Box, BtnL, BtnM, BtnR, ScrlU, ScrlD

  Valid Extensions:
    Shift, Ctrl, Super, Alt, Left, Right, Top, Bottom

  Valid Extensions for Tag:
    Fn:     -
    Fg:     -
    Bg:     -
    Box:    Left, Right, Top, Bottom
    BtnL:   Shift, Ctrl, Super, Alt
    BtnM:   Shift, Ctrl, Super, Alt
    BtnR:   Shift, Ctrl, Super, Alt
    ScrlU:  Shift, Ctrl, Super, Alt
    ScrlD:  Shift, Ctrl, Super, Alt

  Valid values for Tags:
    Fn:     ColorName             (eg. black, #000000)
    Bg:     ColorName             (eg. black, #000000)
    Box:    ColorName:pixelsize   (eg. yellow:1, #cccccc:2)
    BtnL:   Command               (eg. systemctl poweroff)
    BtnM:   Command               (eg. systemctl poweroff)
    BtnR:   Command               (eg. systemctl poweroff)
    ScrlU:  Command               (eg. systemctl poweroff)
    ScrlD:  Command               (eg. systemctl poweroff)

Example text:
-------------
  - <Fg=#131313> Colored </Fg> text with <Bg=#c6c6c6> background</Bg>.

  - <Box:Bottom=#ffffff:1> underlined </Bottom> text.

  - <BtnL=systemctl reboot> reboot </BtnL>

  - <ScrlU:Shift=amixer sset Master 5%+><ScrlD:Shift=amixer sset Master 5%->
      volume
    </ScrlD></ScrlU>
